animal.description:
Evie is a 4-year-old active girl just looking for her next family adventure. She loves to play with her stuffed toys showing her puppy side and enjoys her outdoor walks as well. At 50 pounds she doesn't know she is not a lap dog but really prefers to be. She wants to snuggle with her human all day long if allowed. She can't get enough pets and has fallen asleep under my hand numerous times.. A firm but kind voice is all the correction she needs to guide her in the right direction like when she wants to wrestle with the cat. Evie is just a big Love Bug who needs a lively family of her own who will include her in their daily activities. Evie would do best being the only dog in an adult household or with a similarly active dog.  Additionally, a household with kids, requires they be 12 years and up due to her exuberant energy.Evie is a 4-year-old active girl just looking for her next family adventure. She loves to play with her stuffed toys showing her puppy side and enjoys her outdoor walks as well. At 50 pounds she doesn't know she is not a lap dog but really prefers to be. She wants to snuggle with her human all day long if allowed. She can't get enough pets and has fallen asleep under my hand numerous times.. A firm but kind voice is all the correction she needs to guide her in the right direction like when she wants to wrestle with the cat. Evie is just a big Love Bug who needs a family of her own who will provide her with a daily routine.  She would do best being the only dog or with a gentile calm doggie housemate. Additionally, Evie's ideal home is in an adult household or in a family with respectful children 12 years or older.

(A $300 adoption fee is required.) If you are interested in this dog, please go to the Adopt page of our website where you will find a link to an adoption application form  https://www.chewdogrescue.org/index.php/component/rsform/form/5-adoption-application-form
 
If you have previously submitted an application form, there is no need to re-apply. Just let us know you're interested in this dog. We do our best to match families and dogs so everyone is pleased and the placement is permanent. We reserve the right to refuse an applicant if the home situation is incompatible with the needs of the rescue dog. Rescue is about doing our best for the dog. We do home and reference checks.  All of our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and are up to date with current vaccinations, before being placed in their forever homes.

FOSTER HOMES NEEDED! We are always looking for good foster homes. Our rescue is foster based and we can always save more dogs if we have foster homes for them to go into. It is not a long term commitment. We have been able to find good forever homes in a short time. We also welcome volunteers who can help transport dogs and help with our outreach and fund raising efforts. Please contact us if you can help.

animal.description: Hello, my name is Harley and I’m about 15 months old, neutered and current on all my vaccines.  I’m a loving, sweet and gigantic dog!   At my age I’m still considered a puppy. I’ve come a long way, considering I had no training from my previous owners and when the grand-kids came to live with us I was kicked out the door. I lived my life on a chain during the day and spend my nights in a cold garage. However, life is very different here at the rescue. Once here all of the mats and filth I came with were clipped and washed away.  I stood on the grooming table like a gentleman while I was clipped, bathed and blown dry.  I had a pedicure and my coat is glorious!   I have blossomed and I have been doing well with my training. I like to play with my neighbor dogs and I’m really kind of goofy, but I have a heart of gold. I promise that if you will spend the time to continue my training, it will help me to become the dog you want me to be.  I promise to make you proud of me and will work very hard to please you I am also very handsome, not the least bit shy, and would love to sit in your lap all 109 pounds of me!  I just wanna be with you and like all the dogs here, I just want to be loved and cared about.   I will work very hard to please you. The only thing larger than my stature is my heart and I want to give it to someone who will take good care of it. Is that you?

animal.description:
NO LONGER ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS!

Meet Ava! Someone saw this cute, fluffy puppy standing by a dumpster, all alone, and took her in. They reached out to us to find her a home. She was healthy when we had her checked out, so we suspect she was not on her own for very long.

Ava is currently living in a foster home with teenage kids and another dog. She loves playing with other dogs and would love to have another pup companion in her new home to show her the ropes. Ava's foster mom shared this update:

"Ava is a perfect mix of playful and snuggly. When she's awake, she's energetic, bouncy, curious and wants to be near and touching people. She is mostly quiet using her bark only as a way to tell you she is not done playing yet. She's a great sleeper...She sleeps often and hard throughout the day, and sleeps through the night without a peep. She sleeps in a penned area we have in our family room and will go over to use her pee pee pads 90% of the time. Ava just wants to play with the other dogs and is a very social pup. She comes bounding over to Lily with her tail wagging the whole time. Ava looks like a lab but her fur is thicker and fluffier than a lab. She is mostly black with a couple of tufts of white on her chest and the tips of her paws. She is a very sweet girl."

This pretty girl needs a fun, active family ready for puppy mode and committed to training. She is very cute now but will grow to be a strong and energetic dog who needs a committed handler. Another established, social dog in the home is always helpful for them to learn from, but she's a pretty social pup, and could be an only dog too.

Requirements:

Active family

Large breed dog experience

Flexible, puppy-friendly schedule

Will only be adopted to families in the DC metro and surrounding areas

NOTE: Ava is still too young to be spayed, but having her spayed at the appropriate age will be part of her adoption terms. We will require that proof of spay is provided to the rescue at the appropriate time.

Victoria will be coming to N. VA on 2/6/21, and we plan for her to go straight home. More pics coming soon.

Apply today!

BREED ESTIMATE: Black Lab Mix
GENDER: Female
APPROXIMATE WEIGHT: 7 lbs (will be around 50lbs fully grown)
APPROXIMATE AGE: ~9 weeks
COAT TYPE: medium
ADOPTION FEE: $400
OTHER INFO: UTD on shots/dewormed/microchipped
LOCATION: Rock Hill, SC

FOR MORE INFO OR TO ADOPT: Please go to https://adopt.worthydog.org and complete the application.

You can also help save dogs like this one by becoming a foster, providing a rescue dog with a temporary home and giving them the love and care they need until they are permanently adopted. Every person who fosters is directly responsible for saving the life of a dog, because we can only save as many dogs as we have foster families available to welcome them into their homes. If you think you might be interested in becoming a foster and want to learn more, please go to https://foster.worthydog.org and fill out an application.

Worthy Dog Rescue is an all-volunteer, foster-based rescue that primarily adopts to families in the DC Metro area.

Hi I'm Brent, but my foster mom and dad call me Goob. I was a street dog but I've quickly become a house dog. I love my foster brother, another dog like me. We play so well together. I love love love humans and can get along with pretty much anyone and anything! I love snuggling and giving kisses. I'm very much a loving pup and I can't wait to find my very own family to love on. I don't go too far from my foster family because I love being around them so much. I'm not really sure what "potty trained means but I don't ever do my business inside. I guess because I was a street dog I'm used to doing my business outside! I sleep in my kennel at night and when my foster family isn't in the house because I'm not too confident yet by myself.

Basically, if you're looking for a snuggle bud that loves you unconditionally and is perfectly fine being a couch potato with a walk thrown in there everyday, I am YOUR GUY.

Brent is a Male 2 y/o male Shepherd/Chihuahua mix and weighs 30 lbs

animal.description:
If you're searching for the most devoted and loving best friend ever.... Kai is the pup you want to have around! Kai, at just about 10 months to 1 year old and 45 lbs is just naturally a lover ....when he looks at you with those dark, expressive eyes and sweet smile, your heart just has to melt. Kai is a beautiful Red Heeler/Labrador Retriever mix with all the traits that make these very smart and personality-plus dogs super- popular and beloved breed mixes.
   
Kai enjoys his time with his foster mom so much that he joins her just about everywhere she goes...it's so important to Kai to be a true best friend! Kai cuddles close on the couch (or snuggling close on the bed all night is perfect!) with his beautiful head draped over his favorite person's leg. An occasional kiss from Kai is inevitable. He's a sensitive and very sweet pup who derives so much joy from his time spent with his people and his doggy friends.
 
Kai is a young, healthy guy who will love his family with all his heart. He enjoys canine friends as well and would love nothing more than to play hard and then lie together with his doggy friend in the sunshine enjoying a beautiful day. Kai will have so much fun exploring and taking long walks along the Colorado trails. He is always open to new activities with a never-ending positive attitude...just say the word and up Kai jumps for a car ride, a fun hike or just a sociable walk around the neighborhood. 

Kai'a foster mom had the following to brag about this sweet guy:  Meet Kai, the energetic, super-loving and fun as can be Herding Dog/Retriever mix. Kai was a personal surrender to the shelter from a woman that is taking a new and very demanding job that will require very long hours and trips away from home very often.

Kai is a very sweet and loving guy...he's really good with other dogs and loves to play hard with them. Kai is also great with people.. both adults and children alike! This guy is a strong and energetic pup so therefore most likely better with a family that has older children only or with retirees that love the outdoors..walking, hiking and playing hard with Kai. He would love nothing more than some serious fetch-playing or agility is a natural for this herding dog mix. 

Kai is super-smart (just a natural part of being a Cattle Dog!). He knows sit and down on command and  is also good around food..no aggression or food guarding at all. You can take his food bowl, or ask him to sit while you place his food bowl down, and he will wait until told OK. Kai is also crate trained and house trained as well as very respectful of personal property. This active dog is definitely an exercise outside guy...a very active family that loves to run, hike, snowshoe or any activity that brings a family and dog together would be perfect for Kai!   

Kai is an extremely affectionate and loving dog! We would love to see him in a home with a family (older kids preferred so there's no tail-pulling or awkward handling) or active retirees who have the time and love for a very loyal and kind puppy. We'd hate to see Kai left alone all day while his family works full-time outside of the home...he seems to be too sensitive for that type of arrangement. Kai will thrive on spending the days near his people..getting loved up periodically throughout the day.

Farfel's Rescue would like to see Kai in a home where he'll get consistent stimulation, exercise and tons of loving hugs. A positive reinforcement group training class promotes great behavior, bonding and confidence for a young guy whose self-esteem will fly high while he masters his skills. Training is so important in the future behavior of every dog..it's for this reason that we're unwilling to adopt Kai out to a family that doesn't make this loving choice.  Farfel's is happy to provide a list of positive reinforcement/force- free trainers in your area.
 
Kai has a stunning red merle coat that currently shelter-sad. This beautiful guy will require a lifelong commitment to periodic baths/brushing and excellent nutrition (5 star food and a daily salmon oil supplement are great lifelong protocols for coat care and general health) to keep Kai's coat cottony-soft and super-healthy.
 
Kai will be arriving on transport in Denver on Wednesday 2/10/2020. Applications are currently being accepted for this very sweet, loving and loyal best friend. An application can be found at http://farfels.com/farfels-rescue/adoption-form/. If interested, please fill out completely and submit.

**PLEASE NOTE** If you're truly interested in adopting Kai please be sure to fill out our Farfel's Rescue adoption application found at the link above or at farfels.com. Adoption site applications such as Petfinder, Rescueme and Adoptapet don't provide enough information and therefore aren't useful. Our Farfel's application is the only initial tool that we have to determine a great match for this very deserving dog. We're sorry, but in most cases, we're unable to get back to those that don't submit our Farfel's Rescue adoption application. Thanks very much for choosing rescue.

animal.description:
Patsy is a 1 year old Jack Russell Terrier mix weighing 30 lbs. Patsy has a lot of puppy energy.  Patsy likes to give kisses, loves her belly rubbed, and likes to play with toys that are squeaky or tennis balls. Patsy is crate trained and house trained.

Patsy is unsure of unfamiliar people and new environments so she needs some one to help her get over her fears and requires slow introduction to unfamiliar people.  

Patsy is fostered with a smaller dog and plays well with the smaller dog in her foster home. Patsy is not fostered with small children or cats.  

Patsy is very sweet and loving girl once she gets to know you. Patsy is just waiting to find her forever home. Patsy’s adoption fee is $400.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
NOTE: We update our posts daily. If you are reading this, we are still accepting applications. We will NOT respond to "is he available" inquiries. 

Thiago is a handsome 3-year-old Poodle Mix. He’s the sweetest hero on our squad! He’s a lover! He’s good with other pups and sometimes plays with them, however, prefers the company of humans!

He’s extremely affectionate! He’s a cuddler, loves to be near his human and is an overall good boy! He continues to work on his potty training and does display some separation anxiety. He weighs about 15 lbs.

Thiago is available for adoption. If you are interested in Thiago, please submit an Adoption Interest Application found on our website www.jointhescars.org.

*PLEASE READ: Traditionally, we personally respond to each submission received. However, due to the current high volume of applications/adoptions, you will receive an acknowledgment/receipt email of your submission.

Because we know each of our heroes personally and know the best setting for them to thrive in, we will ONLY contact applications that best match their requisite needs.

We thank you in advance for your interest to adopt one of our heroes and for your patience through the process.

Thank you for choosing to rescue!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
DAISY is a beautiful 8 year old 70 lb. mixed breed girl looking for her furever home. She's a bulldog/pittie mix, plus maybe a little boxer and who knows what else. This girl hasn't had a great life, she's been bounced around to multiple homes and when she came to us she was underweight and her coat told us a tale of neglect. She's put on weight and her coat is looking so much better with good nutrition and veterinary care. She takes a few minutes to warm up to new people. Treats are the best way to win her heart, Daisy is verrrry food motivated. She loves toys and is perfectly content to amuse herself. Daisy is a strong girl and needs work on her leash manners. She's not a big fan of the great outdoors, so she's best suited to a home with a fenced yard where she can run outside, take care of business and get right back inside to her toys. We think she's best suited to a quieter home as an only dog. Daisy is fully housebroken and knows the "sit" command. If you'd like to meet Daisy, please fill out a foster-to-adopt application at
dreamhouserescue.org.

All of our fully-vetted adoptable dogs go to prospective homes for a one-week trial foster-to-adopt period to make sure the dog and home are the right fit before an adoption is finalized. We only adopt dogs into homes where all current pets are spayed/neutered and current on vaccines and heartworm and flea and tick prevention. We do check veterinary references to make sure adopters are compliant with standard veterinary care.
animal.name: Daisy

animal.description:
Meet Shep!

This poor boy was found by one of our veterinarians. Sadly, he was lying with his friend who had been hit and killed by a car. He has been vaccinated, dewormed and neutered. He has been started on slow kill heartworm treatment. He is exhibiting a bit of anxiety at the vet clinic but who can blame him. He was most likely dumped with his buddy, saw his buddy hit and killed and now is in an unknown place. And he is probably just about a year and a half old, not even a grown up. One of the vet techs is going to try taking him home to foster to see if that helps. So we should know more about him soon.

If you would like to give this boy the life he should have had from the beginning please complete our application,
www.scoutshonor.org
